<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-634-920  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 634 920.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 5 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Online Japanese-to-English database.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken; Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Fujitsu Ltd. (product development)Fujitsu Facom Information Processing (product development)Fujitsu America Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentLanguage TranslationJapanese LanguageSearchingSoftware packagesSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ONLINE JAPANESE-TO-ENGLISH DATABASE TOKYO, JAPAN, 1989 AUG 30 (NB) -- Withthe pace of technological change occurring at record speed, information onthese changes is in increasing demand, but until now language barriers havekept most people away from all but their own country's developments.andP;  A newproduct hopes to change that.andP;  Fujitsu, Fujitsu FIP (for Facom InformationProcessing), and Fujitsu America have jointly developed online databasesoftware and a new mainframe-based online system for retrieving technologyinformation, combined with a machine translation system.andP;  Unveiled at theWorld Computer Congress in San Francisco, California this week, Scanfileenables a user to search data by entering English keywords.andP;  The systemautomatically translates the keywords to Japanese, retrieves articles writtenin Japanese, then translates and outputs the text in English.andP;  Scanfile isbased on the artificial intelligence ATLA translation system, and datatransmission technology.andP;  Fujitsu says a single article can be retrieved andtranslated via telephone lines on average in about 80 seconds.andP;  It requiresno knowledge of the Japanese language to operate.andP;  Expected to becommercially available in 1990, Scanfile currently is being used online forthe VAN (value-added network) service managed by Fujitsu FIP in Japan.andP;  Itcan be accessed by any terminal or PC.andP;  The FIP service is the largestvalue-added network in Japan, serving an estimated 80,000 users.andP;  (KenTakahashi andamp; Wendy Woods/19890831)</TEXT></DOC>